<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}-{9}{y}=-{51}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{4}{y}={18}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -6. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{-{{3}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{6}}}{{-{{3}}}}{\left(-{3}{x}+-{9}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{6}}}{{-{{3}}}}{\left(-{51}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({6}\right)}{x}+-{18}{y}=-{102}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{4}{y}={18}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{14}{y}=-{84}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{84}}{{-{{14}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+-{9}{\left({6}\right)}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{\left(-{54}\right)}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}=-{51}-{\left(-{54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}={3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{3}}{{-{{3}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

